This book was edited by Heather E. Umphlett, Camp Community College. Development of this book was 
supported, in part, by the Summer Technology Grant for Summer 2019, and updated as needed. This 
book was built upon and creates using the following sources:
Math in Society edition 2.5 by David Lippman, Pierce College Ft Steilacoom. Sections from Problem 
Solving, Growth Models, Finance, Sets, and Logic were all used and slightly altered to fit this 
book. Math in Society is covered under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 United States 
License.
Algebra and Trigonometry from OpenStax, with senior contributing author Jay Abram-son, Arizona 
State University. Sections from Exponential and Logarithmic Functions, as well as Fitting Linear 
Models to Data, and Quadratic Functions, were all used and altered to fit this book and content 
level. Algebra and Trigonometry is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International.
Elementary Algebra from OpenStax, with senior contributing authors Lynn Marecek, Santa Ana College 
and MaryAnne Anthony-Smith, formerly of Santa Ana College. Sections from Graphs, and Systems of 
Equations, were used and altered to fit this book and content level. Elementary Algebra is licensed 
under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International.
Chapter 3 Conversions from Clark Smith of Glendale Community College Chemistry 130. Content covered 
under Creative Commons Attributions 4.0 Share Alike ( CC-BY-SA 4.0). Information from this section 
was used and altered to make up Chapter 5 of this text.
Other sources for this book are sited as footnotes throughout the text.
